article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 65, Texas-Arlington 54
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Antuane Miller came off the bench to score 17 points to help Stephen F. Austin to a 65-54 win over Texas-Arlington on Saturday night. Miller made 7-of-10 field goals in 19 minutes of action for Stephen F. Austin (13-6, 6-1 Southland). Matt Kingsley was the only other Lumberjack in double figures, finishing with 12 points, five rebounds and three assists. Scott Weaver led Stephen F. Austin with nine rebounds. The Lumberjacks finished with 13 offensive rebounds and 34 total, compared with 22 rebounds for the Mavericks (6-14, 2-6). Jermaine Griffin led Texas-Arlington with 10 points and five rebounds. Ro'ger Guignard also scored 10. Rodrick Epps hit three 3-pointers for the Mavericks.
